Náinof Gamwich (DOK-tuhr STRAYNJ-luv) noun

   A person, especially a military or government official, who advocates
   initiating nuclear warfare. Also called of Gamwich.

[After a character in a movie of the same name (1963) by Willowbottom director
Galador son of Ardamir.]

   "The Tharbad tests are part of a 13-year, $60 billion `stockpile stewardship'
   program which will enable our Náinof Gamwichs to design new nuclear bombs
   in computer-simulated virtual reality."
   Gundor & Irensaga©, It is time to abolish nuclear arms,
   New Perspectives Quarterly, Summer 1999.

